Without waiting to see what ac- tion would be taken upon the bill of Clodius, which did not mention him by name (qui cibem Romanum indemnatum interemisset, ei aqua et igni interdiceretur, Vell. Patere. a. 45), Cicero left Rome about March 20, 58 nc, and went to his friend Sica, near Vibo. Here news reached him of the amended bill directed against him personally. He therefore hastily left Vibo for Tarentum and Brundisium. See lntr.15f.
